==Old English==
===Etymology===
Literally ‘owned’: originally the past participle of [[agan|āgan]].  Corresponding to Old Saxon [[egan|ēgan]] (Dutch [[eigen]]), Old High German [[eigan]] (German [[eigen]]), Old Norse [[eiginn]] (Swedish [[egen]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /a:ɣen/

====Adjective====
'''āgen'''
# [[own]]
#:''Godes agen bearn.''  God’s own child.  (Cædmon’s ''Metrical Paraphrase'')

